35 const char* const reactionTypeString(const ReactionType type)
36 {
37  switch (type) {
38  case ASSOCIATIVE_IONIZATION:
39  return "associative ionization";
40  case DISSOCIATIVE_RECOMBINATION:
41  return "dissociative recombination";
42  case ASSOCIATIVE_DETACHMENT:
43  return "associative detachment";
44  case DISSOCIATIVE_ATTACHMENT:
45  return "dissociative attachment";
46  case DISSOCIATION_M:
47  return "heavy particle impact dissociation";
48  case DISSOCIATION_E:
49  return "electron impact dissociation";
50  case RECOMBINATION_M:
51  return "heavy particle impact recombination";
52  case RECOMBINATION_E:
53  return "electron impact recombination";
54  case IONIZATION_M:
55  return "heavy particle impact ionization";
56  case IONIZATION_E:
57  return "electron impact ionization";
58  case ION_RECOMBINATION_M:
59  return "heavy particle impact ion recombination";
60  case ION_RECOMBINATION_E:
61  return "electron impact ion recombination";
62  case ELECTRONIC_ATTACHMENT_E:
63  return "electron impact electron attachment";
64  case ELECTRONIC_DETACHMENT_E:
65  return "electron impact electron detachment";
66  case ELECTRONIC_ATTACHMENT_M:
67  return "heavy particle impact electron attachment";
68  case ELECTRONIC_DETACHMENT_M:
69  return "heavy particle impact electron detachment";
70  case EXCHANGE:
71  return "exchange";
72  case EXCITATION_E:
73  return "electron impact excitation/deexcitation";
74  case EXCITATION_M:
75  return "heavy particle impact excitation/deexcitation";
76  default:
77  return "unknown type";
78  }
79 }
